00:32.783 --> 00:34.158
Let's get started.

00:34.243 --> 00:36.285
First I'd like to announce
that thanks to the magic

00:36.370 --> 00:38.037
of Disney Animatronics,

00:38.122 --> 00:40.873
Strom Thurmond will
live another 100 years.

00:43.460 --> 00:45.378
Twenty more terms!

00:45.629 --> 00:49.215
Moving on to new business,
what act of unmitigated evil

00:49.299 --> 00:51.217
shall the Republican
Party undertake this week?

00:51.301 --> 00:52.593
Oh! Oh, oh, oh.

00:53.178 --> 00:55.012
You've already done enough, Nader.

00:55.180 --> 00:57.181
Let's get rid of PBS!

00:57.266 --> 00:58.599
Those lousy Muppets have been taking

00:58.684 --> 01:00.643
food out of my mouth for too long!

01:01.979 --> 01:04.605
I say we crack down on the hippies.

01:04.815 --> 01:05.815
Bla.

01:05.899 --> 01:07.900
What about this dang environment?

01:07.985 --> 01:10.236
Back in Texas, we got rid of it,

01:10.320 --> 01:12.363
and it made everyone a lot happier.

01:13.157 --> 01:14.449
He was so happy...

01:14.533 --> 01:15.742
Excellent.

01:15.826 --> 01:17.577
We shall destroy the environment

01:17.661 --> 01:19.746
by scrapping every anti-pollution law.

01:20.164 --> 01:24.459
Now Bob Dole will read
from the Necronomicon.

01:32.009 --> 01:34.343
In addition, the
administration has declared

01:34.428 --> 01:36.429
recycling a felony.

01:36.513 --> 01:40.016
And Smokey the Bear is
now Choppy the Lumberjack.

01:41.351 --> 01:43.728
These trees are our national heritage!

01:48.525 --> 01:50.735
A grizzly bear with a chainsaw.

01:50.861 --> 01:53.070
Now there's a killing machine!

02:00.037 --> 02:03.873
Stop endangering yourself.
Stop endangering yourself.

02:31.068 --> 02:32.568
Eyes stinging!

02:33.403 --> 02:35.196
Good Lord! Acid rain!

02:35.447 --> 02:38.449
I'm singing in the rain

02:38.534 --> 02:43.913
Just singing in the rain
What a glorious feeling

02:45.207 --> 02:48.584
It burns like a Glasgow bikini wax!

02:51.797 --> 02:56.133
We'd better stay inside, at least
until the squirrels stop melting.

02:56.218 --> 03:00.263
No problem. There's plenty
of activities inside.

03:01.473 --> 03:04.725
Now let's see how our blind
dates liked each other.

03:05.310 --> 03:06.894
Oh, I really felt
there was a connection,

03:06.979 --> 03:09.438
and I would definitely
go out with her again.

03:09.523 --> 03:11.107
He smelled like puke!

03:13.777 --> 03:14.861
The TV!

03:29.001 --> 03:30.501
Stop screaming, Homer.

03:30.627 --> 03:32.169
Quit trying to control me.

03:32.254 --> 03:34.839
We don't need TV to have family fun.

03:34.923 --> 03:37.383
Why don't we play Monopoly?

03:37.718 --> 03:38.926
Which version?

03:39.094 --> 03:41.095
We've got Star Wars Monopoly.

03:46.143 --> 03:48.644
Let's stick to original Monopoly.

03:48.812 --> 03:51.272
The game is crazy enough as it is.

03:51.356 --> 03:53.691
How can an iron be a landlord?

03:55.819 --> 03:57.153
Pennsylvania Avenue.

03:57.237 --> 04:00.156
I want to buy a house.
Hey, where'd they go?

04:01.450 --> 04:02.909
New shooter!

04:05.370 --> 04:08.664
That's it, baby. Welcome
to Marvin Gardens.

04:08.749 --> 04:12.793
We'll see about that. One, two, three...

04:12.878 --> 04:13.878
D'oh!

04:17.423 --> 04:19.050
You're a little light here, Dad.

04:19.134 --> 04:21.052
I'm good for the rest. You know I am.

04:21.136 --> 04:22.637
Well, I'd like to trust you, Homer.

04:22.721 --> 04:25.222
But you've been in jail three times.

04:25.307 --> 04:28.017
They told me it would be
like this on the outside.

04:29.353 --> 04:33.272
These hotels are made of
Legos. Bart, you're cheating!

04:33.357 --> 04:35.608
Lisa, it was probably an accident.

04:35.692 --> 04:37.610
Oh, sure. You take his side

04:37.694 --> 04:40.738
just because he bought you
that house on St. James Place.

04:40.822 --> 04:43.783
Who else is gonna take care of her? Dad?

04:43.867 --> 04:46.327
Why you little...

04:46.411 --> 04:47.787
Stop fighting!

04:47.871 --> 04:50.414
Mom, that's not how you pry them apart.

04:50.499 --> 04:55.002
I've been prying them apart
since before you were born!

05:08.600 --> 05:10.601
Okay. Everyone turn to the left.

05:11.853 --> 05:13.521
Hey! Oh, come on, people.

05:13.605 --> 05:16.524
The Prison Nutcracker
Suite is one week away.

05:16.608 --> 05:18.734
And I don't see five Sugar Plums.

05:18.819 --> 05:20.820
I see five guys who don't know

05:20.904 --> 05:22.655
their moves and don't seem to care!

05:22.739 --> 05:24.073
There, I said it!

05:25.492 --> 05:26.867
That better be Wardrobe.

05:26.952 --> 05:28.744
And it better be good news.

05:28.870 --> 05:30.413
Hello?

05:30.998 --> 05:33.165
It sounds like a domestic disturbance.

05:33.250 --> 05:34.583
All right. We'll be right back.

05:34.668 --> 05:38.504
And don't try anything, because
Johanssen there is a snitch.

05:51.893 --> 05:55.229
Another case of
Monopoly-related violence, Chief.

05:55.605 --> 05:58.065
How do those Parker
Brothers sleep at night?

06:00.193 --> 06:02.111
We better send in the Negotia-bot.

06:06.950 --> 06:09.577
I am Brenda. I am programmed to talk

06:09.661 --> 06:11.829
in a calm and constructive manner.

06:11.913 --> 06:14.623
Destroy! Destroy!

06:19.421 --> 06:21.130
Hey, this is taffy!

06:21.214 --> 06:23.090
Police brutality!

06:25.302 --> 06:27.011
And chew-tality!

06:32.768 --> 06:35.061
Nice work, Brenda.
I'll take it from here.

06:35.145 --> 06:37.313
No way. This is my collar.

06:38.982 --> 06:42.151
Too bad real women don't
come with these, huh?

06:44.571 --> 06:46.447
You got that right. Quiet, you!

06:46.531 --> 06:48.199
That counts as your phone call.

06:55.707 --> 06:56.916
Thanks a lot, everybody.

06:57.000 --> 06:59.585
Now, I'll never get into
an Ivy League school.

06:59.669 --> 07:04.757
You're going to Stanford.
You're going to Stanford.

07:04.841 --> 07:06.592
Take it back! Take it back!

07:06.718 --> 07:10.179
Stanford. This family
has hit rock bottom.

07:16.311 --> 07:18.187
Hello. I'm Gabriel.

07:18.355 --> 07:22.274
A heavenly choir. You must be an angel!

07:23.693 --> 07:25.277
No. That's my pager.

07:25.362 --> 07:27.321
I'm a social worker.

07:27.447 --> 07:30.908
I'm here to help you stop
fighting and become a family again.

07:30.992 --> 07:33.119
No. You are an angel.

07:33.203 --> 07:35.704
Like Denzel Washington
in The Preacher's Wife,

07:35.789 --> 07:41.669
or Will Smith in Bagger Vance,
or Slimer in Ghostbusters.

07:41.753 --> 07:43.879
Sir, we know you're not an angel.

07:43.964 --> 07:46.173
My husband sees too many movies.

07:46.341 --> 07:50.469
Don't blame me. Blame Tinseltown
in its second golden age,

07:50.554 --> 07:52.221
may it never end.

07:53.807 --> 07:55.808
In a difficult case like this,

07:55.892 --> 07:58.978
I like to observe each
family member individually.

07:59.062 --> 08:01.188
Well, my room is my sanctuary.

08:01.273 --> 08:03.983
My family knows that and respects that.

08:04.067 --> 08:06.902
I got sprayed by a skunk! Let
me rub it off on your sweaters!

08:07.696 --> 08:10.489
Just 10 more years. Just 10 more years.

08:10.574 --> 08:12.491
Just 10 more years.

08:13.535 --> 08:18.497
Attention, everyone. This is
Gabriel, my personal social worker.

08:18.582 --> 08:21.208
He has to be here. I'm just that nuts.

08:23.712 --> 08:25.796
How come you get a social worker?

08:25.881 --> 08:27.923
I'm the one with stigmata.

08:31.052 --> 08:33.929
Thank you, Marge. You
sure do love cooking.

08:34.014 --> 08:36.222
Food keeps my family happy.

08:36.308 --> 08:39.268
So, I make a few practice
dinners before showtime.

08:39.352 --> 08:42.520
Because at 6:00, we go live!

08:45.859 --> 08:49.111
Ah! Okay, Gabriel, this is a bar.

08:49.196 --> 08:50.988
It's where I go to drink alcohol,

08:51.072 --> 08:54.158
which is the mortal
equivalent of your ambrosia.

08:54.284 --> 08:56.535
Homer, I am not an angel!

08:56.620 --> 08:58.871
Well, not with that temper.

09:01.917 --> 09:06.921
Look, the thing about my
family is there's five of us.

09:07.005 --> 09:10.049
Marge, Bart, Girl Bart,

09:10.133 --> 09:14.428
the one who doesn't
talk, and the fat guy.

09:14.512 --> 09:16.722
How I loathe him!

09:18.516 --> 09:19.892
Oh!

09:23.563 --> 09:26.440
Okay. Why are we in the woods?

09:26.524 --> 09:28.984
Is this heaven? No.

09:29.069 --> 09:30.527
I brought you out here to shake off

09:30.612 --> 09:32.613
your negative behavior patterns.

09:32.697 --> 09:35.741
Marge, you medicate
your family with food.

09:35.825 --> 09:38.244
Bart, you'll do anything for attention.

09:38.328 --> 09:39.411
Cut that out!

09:39.496 --> 09:40.996
They chose me.

09:41.790 --> 09:43.999
Homer, your problem is quite simple.

09:44.292 --> 09:46.293
You're a drunken, childish buffoon.

09:46.378 --> 09:49.588
Which is society's fault because...

09:49.673 --> 09:52.841
It's your fault, Homer.
But I've got an exercise

09:52.926 --> 09:55.594
that will help all of you break
out of the roles you're stuck in.

09:55.679 --> 09:56.929
Who feels like lunch? Me!

09:57.013 --> 09:58.055
Me! Right here!

09:58.139 --> 09:59.473
Me, too! Good.

09:59.557 --> 10:01.016
I hung it on the top of that tree.

10:02.310 --> 10:03.852
But how are we supposed to get it?

10:03.937 --> 10:05.938
You'll just have to cooperate.

10:06.022 --> 10:07.523
Cooperate?

10:07.607 --> 10:11.485
Well, this is one family
that doesn't swing that way!

10:12.070 --> 10:13.237
Are you sure?

10:13.321 --> 10:15.030
I made roast beef sandwiches,

10:15.115 --> 10:16.657
one falafel... Thank you.

10:16.741 --> 10:17.783
...and plenty of beer.

10:17.867 --> 10:18.951
Give me that beer!

10:36.803 --> 10:38.637
Gabriel, are you okay?

10:39.014 --> 10:41.140
Yes. But I'm afraid your lunch

10:41.224 --> 10:43.392
has attracted some unwanted visitors.

10:46.563 --> 10:49.273
We've got to do something! But what?

10:49.357 --> 10:50.607
Okay, family huddle.

10:51.526 --> 10:53.068
Here's how it's gonna go down.

10:53.486 --> 10:55.446
As a family, we drive away.

10:55.530 --> 10:58.407
We cover for each other as a family.

10:58.616 --> 11:00.117
That's what Gabriel would've wanted.

11:00.201 --> 11:02.119
Look. We can't fall into old patterns.

11:02.203 --> 11:03.829
We've got to think of a plan.

11:03.913 --> 11:06.540
Okay. But talk like this.

11:06.624 --> 11:08.584
Fine. I'll talk like this.

11:08.668 --> 11:09.710
What?

11:12.464 --> 11:15.257
Look, Gabriel! We're
learning to work together!

11:15.342 --> 11:17.760
That's great. But so are
the wolves and cougars!

11:28.938 --> 11:33.108
Dad's on the log. Now, Mom, you
get the car and pull them to safety!

11:33.443 --> 11:37.154
My driving ankle.

11:38.114 --> 11:40.574
Bart, I know this sounds crazy,

11:40.658 --> 11:42.868
but do you think you can drive a car?

11:42.952 --> 11:45.329
Okay. But it's my first time.

11:45.622 --> 11:46.789
Here's the keys.

11:46.873 --> 11:47.873
I got a set.

11:58.760 --> 11:59.968
Now, Bart!

12:08.812 --> 12:10.145
Give them the food!

12:15.652 --> 12:18.320
Oh, no! The roast beef
is making them stronger!

12:18.405 --> 12:20.572
And the falafel is making them angrier!

12:24.702 --> 12:26.412
Give them the beer!

12:26.496 --> 12:28.288
It will impair their motor skills!

12:28.373 --> 12:30.833
No! I will never...

12:30.917 --> 12:32.251
Oh, wait. It's Blatz.

12:40.552 --> 12:42.261
Hey, they're all right.

12:42.345 --> 12:44.847
We are family

12:44.931 --> 12:47.683
Our bitter fights are now history

12:47.767 --> 12:50.269
We are family

12:50.353 --> 12:52.813
Wolves and cougars ate our roast beef

12:52.897 --> 12:55.441
Well, I think you all did great.

12:55.525 --> 12:56.859
You broke out of your normal roles

12:56.943 --> 12:59.236
to accomplish something as a family.

12:59.320 --> 13:01.155
I really earned my wings.

13:01.239 --> 13:02.448
I knew it!

13:02.532 --> 13:04.700
No. I mean this CD.

13:08.496 --> 13:10.706
Band on the run

13:10.915 --> 13:15.210
You know, we've been through
some 280 adventures together,

13:15.295 --> 13:18.297
but our bond has never been stronger.

13:18.381 --> 13:19.381
Mmm.

13:19.883 --> 13:23.635
Yeah. Our family is as
functional as all get out.

13:23.720 --> 13:28.056
Could this be the end
of our series of events?

13:32.770 --> 13:34.521
Can I help you?

13:34.606 --> 13:36.899
Yeah. I'm looking for Homer Simpson.

13:38.359 --> 13:41.069
Oh, it's the woman I married in Vegas!

13:42.572 --> 13:44.907
Homer, you're a bad man,

13:44.991 --> 13:47.201
and your seed should
be wiped from the earth.

13:47.827 --> 13:49.286
No offense, children.

13:56.252 --> 13:59.129
Homer and Ned, you may
now kiss your brides.

13:59.756 --> 14:01.632
Give it to me, baby.

14:02.675 --> 14:05.260
Homer! It's okay! We're married!

14:06.471 --> 14:09.223
You and Ned married
a couple of floozies?

14:09.307 --> 14:12.184
Marge, I'm sorry! But
it wasn't my fault.

14:12.268 --> 14:13.685
Liquors drunkened me!

14:13.770 --> 14:16.230
If I had known there were
loose women in Las Vegas,

14:16.314 --> 14:18.357
I would never have let you go!

14:18.441 --> 14:21.068
Look, I did marry her!
But I abandoned her!

14:21.152 --> 14:23.403
Amber, tell her how I abandoned you!

14:23.488 --> 14:25.614
This is the worst
thing you've ever done!

14:29.244 --> 14:31.161
Well, Ginger,

14:31.246 --> 14:34.456
it sure is neat that you
managed to hunt me down.

14:34.541 --> 14:36.083
Where's the bed?

14:36.167 --> 14:39.878
Oh Lord, I know my new
wife is a little more

14:39.963 --> 14:41.171
peppermint than you're used to.

14:41.256 --> 14:44.883
But I know you'd want me to
honor my sacred vows. So, I will.

14:44.968 --> 14:48.345
Hey, stud. Where do you keep
your Wet Ones? I need a shower.

14:48.429 --> 14:50.722
Oh, we've got a real shower upstairs.

14:50.807 --> 14:53.225
Upstairs? I hit the jackpot!

14:57.814 --> 15:01.233
So, sitting on the bed, eh?

15:01.317 --> 15:03.151
Get out, Homer.

15:03.861 --> 15:06.822
Look, I married her. But
that is as far as we went.

15:06.906 --> 15:09.783
We never ever made whoopee,
or even mouth whoopee!

15:10.034 --> 15:13.078
Homer, I don't know if
I can ever forgive you.

15:13.162 --> 15:14.913
Please go away.

15:14.998 --> 15:16.039
Fair enough.

15:16.124 --> 15:17.874
But I'm gonna come back
with the greatest gift

15:17.959 --> 15:21.920
a husband can give his wife. An
annulment from his secret wife.

15:23.339 --> 15:28.427
Mr. Simpson, under Nevada law,
bigamy, or "Mormon Hold 'Em,"

15:28.511 --> 15:31.513
is perfectly legal.
Both marriages stand.

15:31.723 --> 15:33.599
But I only love Marge!

15:33.683 --> 15:36.893
I hereby order you to take
care of both of your wives!

15:36.978 --> 15:38.312
Bailiff, ring him!

15:45.862 --> 15:50.490
You can't kick me out. It'll
cause a miscount in the census!

15:50.575 --> 15:52.075
A miscount!

15:54.579 --> 15:55.954
Of all things to ever come back

15:56.039 --> 15:58.415
and bite me in the
ass, this is the worst!

16:02.045 --> 16:04.046
Please, just leave me alone.

16:04.130 --> 16:07.966
Now, now. Mama's gonna make you a snack.

16:08.051 --> 16:09.301
Ooh!

16:10.303 --> 16:12.888
Oh, yeah. That's good.

16:12.972 --> 16:15.891
Don't stop. Oh, yeah...

16:15.975 --> 16:19.186
Faster! Faster! Faster!

16:19.270 --> 16:22.648
Faster! Oh, you do that like a pro!

16:22.732 --> 16:26.735
Oh, no. She's making him a sandwich!

16:26.819 --> 16:28.028
Use both hands!

16:30.406 --> 16:35.035
Rise and shine and give
God your glory, glory!

16:36.788 --> 16:38.705
Me and the boys made
you breakfast in bed.

16:38.790 --> 16:39.915
It's the best darn-diddily way

16:39.999 --> 16:42.042
to start your first Flanders day.

16:43.294 --> 16:45.003
Think you can Irish
up this coffee for me?

16:45.088 --> 16:47.089
Oops. Watch the swears, honey bear.

16:47.423 --> 16:49.591
We don't use the "I" word in this house.

16:51.260 --> 16:52.427
Where's my cigarettes?

16:52.512 --> 16:55.013
We flushed your sin sticks down to hell.

16:55.098 --> 16:56.848
Smokers are jokers.

16:56.933 --> 16:58.684
Smokers are jokers! Smokers are jokers!

16:58.768 --> 17:00.519
I think I'm gonna throw up.

17:02.397 --> 17:04.021
Who wants to hold Mommy's hair?

17:04.107 --> 17:05.523
Me! Me! I do!

17:06.651 --> 17:10.362
Hey, Vegas Mom, how long
are you gonna stay here?

17:10.445 --> 17:14.116
I'm not going anywhere. I
already unpacked my delicates.

17:15.367 --> 17:17.911
Doesn't it bother you that
you're breaking up our family?

17:18.287 --> 17:21.248
You know, I bet you
and me could be friends.

17:21.332 --> 17:23.250
I could show you how to put on makeup.

17:23.334 --> 17:25.042
I'm eight years old.

17:25.127 --> 17:26.795
You could look seven.

17:26.963 --> 17:29.256
And I could teach you to count cards.

17:29.340 --> 17:30.966
Nah. I already got a system.

17:31.634 --> 17:32.801
Jeez, Homer. I thought someone

17:32.885 --> 17:34.553
with two wives would be happy.

17:34.637 --> 17:36.805
No. You're thinking of
someone with two knives.

17:37.306 --> 17:39.474
I gotta tell you, this
is pretty terrific.

17:39.559 --> 17:41.268
Yeah!

18:06.586 --> 18:08.962
Can't panic. Must remain calm.

18:23.978 --> 18:26.563
Ah! The sweet couple of seconds before

18:26.647 --> 18:29.399
I remember why I'm sleeping on the lawn.

18:29.692 --> 18:32.235
Homer? Marge, you're speaking to me?

18:32.320 --> 18:34.279
Why don't you come
inside and we'll talk?

18:34.363 --> 18:37.240
Talk about what? Sports? Bigamy?

18:37.325 --> 18:39.201
Bigamy!

18:39.285 --> 18:40.619
Not a sports fan, huh?

18:43.748 --> 18:46.041
You insensitive jerk!

18:46.125 --> 18:49.336
Maybe this family would
be better off without you!

18:49.879 --> 18:52.255
You know, there are only so many times

18:52.340 --> 18:55.091
I can say I'm sorry and still mean it!

18:55.176 --> 18:58.595
Why don't you just take Britney
Beers and get out of here?

18:58.679 --> 19:01.389
I would, if it wasn't for the kids!

19:01.474 --> 19:03.600
Hey, the heart wants
what it wants, dude.

19:03.684 --> 19:05.185
We had a good run.

19:07.980 --> 19:10.315
Well, that's the last we'll see of them.

19:10.691 --> 19:13.068
Come on. We're going to Moe's.

19:16.989 --> 19:18.865
My lady's glass is empty, Moe.

19:18.950 --> 19:21.451
Bring her another
Cookies and Cream martini.

19:21.536 --> 19:25.997
No, honey. This time make
it a Sex on the Beach.

19:26.082 --> 19:28.416
And hold the Beach!

19:29.585 --> 19:32.003
Hey, Homer. Your new wife is great.

19:32.088 --> 19:34.005
Her lips look like night crawlers!

19:34.090 --> 19:36.967
You know, she can put that
mole anywhere on her face.

19:37.051 --> 19:38.218
Wow.

19:38.302 --> 19:43.056
To Amber, who proves there are
seconds in the buffet of life.

19:49.897 --> 19:53.483
Oh, my head! Aspirin.

19:55.444 --> 19:57.320
RU-486.

19:58.865 --> 20:00.657
Morning, love muffin.

20:00.741 --> 20:01.950
Who are you?

20:02.034 --> 20:03.285
I'm your new husband.

20:03.411 --> 20:06.121
And that was a wedding
night I'll never forget!

20:06.414 --> 20:08.206
Oh, no. We didn't.

20:08.291 --> 20:10.250
Well, we almost didn't.

20:10.501 --> 20:13.628
But you wouldn't take
"I can't" for an answer.

20:13.713 --> 20:17.632
You want to give Honest Abe
another term in the Oval Office?

20:17.717 --> 20:18.717
No!

20:18.801 --> 20:19.885
Oh, thank God!

20:22.972 --> 20:25.140
We're married? But how?

20:26.142 --> 20:30.270
Do you, Amber, take Abraham
as your lawful wedded husband,

20:30.354 --> 20:32.480
renouncing all others?

20:32.607 --> 20:34.733
Oh, sure.

20:34.817 --> 20:36.776
He paid for the hour.

20:38.529 --> 20:40.113
Whoo-hoo!

20:40.197 --> 20:41.948
You crapped out, Vegas Mom!

20:42.033 --> 20:44.492
Our plan worked perfectly.

20:44.577 --> 20:46.745
And we carried it out as a family.

20:46.829 --> 20:48.997
What plan? You got me drunk.

20:49.081 --> 20:52.876
Yeah. But this time you woke
up with more than a hangover!

20:52.960 --> 20:55.837
You're married to me! Me!

20:59.258 --> 21:01.676
I can't take it!
You're too goody-goody!

21:01.761 --> 21:04.596
That's not you talking. That's
the honey-mustard dressing!

21:04.680 --> 21:07.265
Come on, Ginger. Let's go back to Vegas.

21:07.350 --> 21:10.685
Yeah. I'm sure there's
poker games we can be won in.

21:15.942 --> 21:17.776
I'm so proud of us.

21:17.860 --> 21:20.779
When we stick together,
we can do anything.

21:20.863 --> 21:23.698
Oh! I lost another wife!

21:23.783 --> 21:25.659
I'm so sorry, Grampa.

21:25.743 --> 21:29.496
Well, it hurts now. But the
senility will take care of that.

21:30.373 --> 21:32.374
There she goes.

21:32.458 --> 21:35.251
You know, I have a son about your age.

21:39.006 --> 21:40.632
Oh, I love that.

